race.description: Kia Ora Bloodlines To Headlines Handicap (Bm72)
race.comment: ZULFIQAR (1) continues to race well deep into his campaign. Made late inroads to finish just 2.4 lengths away in a 1200m Highway at Randwick last time. Has raced just once at this distance for a win - it's taken a while for them to have another try and the move might pay off. CUBAN CIGAR (10) has enjoyed a 39-day let-up since a dogged win in a BM64 over this distance at Kembla. Lightly raced three-year-old who might go to another level again with blinkers on for the first time. EXTRA HEIGHTS (9) was poor last start at Canterbury over 1250m. Might need this journey now so give this sparingly raced colt another chance. Waller brings TARZING (6) to NSW undefeated. Made up a stack of ground to score over a slightly shorter trip at Geelong last time. Takes a big step forward today but cannot be underestimated. SARRISMO (8) is back from a three-month spell. Has scored at both first-up appearances, last prep leading all the way to salute by four at Hawkesbury. Right in contention.
